5.5 Limitations and Future Extensions
The present model is intentionally minimal to isolate the SOC network dynamics.
Important extensions for future work include:
1. Spatial embedding: Placing the network on a 2-D or 3-D lattice to model tissue
geometry and contact mechanics.
2. Immune response: Adding a population of immune cells that preferentially target
high-degree (hub) cancerous nodes, creating a competing cascade of clearance.
3. Drug pharmacokinetics: Modelling drug action as a time-varying reduction in ρ
or increase in ν, allowing optimal timing studies.
4. Metastasis: Extending the model to a multi-tissue network to study when and
how invasion crosses tissue boundaries.
5. Calibration to data: Fitting α, θ, and ρ to clone-size distributions from patient
tumour sequencing data.
